    "45 and 46, the magnetic field has little effect on the entropy production rate contributed by the NOMF, but has a strong inhibition effect on the entropy production rate contributed by the NOEF.",
    "The minimum value of can be used as a physical criterion to determine the critical magnetic field strength under which the RMI interface amplitude could be reduced to 0.5.12 Plasma KHI χp Song et al. [120] introduced tracer particles into DBM to study the influence of magnetic field on the transport and mixing characteristics of plasma KHI, as well as the influence of magnetic field on various kinetic behaviors.",
    "Preliminary results are as follows: (i) For the cases of weak magnetic fields, the magnetic field could inhibit the development of KHI at an early stage, but will lead to the formation of small-scale vortex structure and cause the KHI to enter the mixing stage earlier.",
    "The degree of mixing decreases in the early stage but increases in the later stage.",
    "(ii) For the cases of strong magnetic fields, the development of KHI is significantly inhibited, and the mixing degree is greatly reduced."
